<body>

<header>
    <h1>Cutting Board Plans</h1>
    <p>Your complete guide to building a beautiful wood cutting board</p>
</header>

<div class="container">

    <h2>Materials</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>1 board: 1 in x 8 in x 8 ft (Walnut, Maple, Cherry, etc.)</li>
        <li>Wood glue</li>
        <li>Food-grade mineral oil</li>
        <li>Sandpaper: 80, 120, 220, 400 grit</li>
        <li>Clamps</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Tools</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Table saw or circular saw</li>
        <li>Planer (optional)</li>
        <li>Orbital sander</li>
        <li>Router (optional)</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Cutting Board Build Steps</h2>

    <div class="step">
        <div class="step-title">Step 1 — Cut Into Strips</div>
        <p>Rip the 8 ft board into strips between 1"–1.5" wide.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
        <div class="step-title">Step 2 — Arrange Your Pattern</div>
        <p>Lay out the strips in the order you like (alternating colors looks great).</p>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
        <div class="step-title">Step 3 — Glue the Strips</div>
        <p>Apply wood glue to all edges and clamp for at least 4 hours.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
        <div class="step-title">Step 4 — Flatten the Board</div>
        <p>Use a planer or sander to smooth both faces.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
        <div class="step-title">Step 5 — Trim to Final Size</div>
        <p>Square the edges with a table saw.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
        <div class="step-title">Step 6 — Sand Smooth</div>
        <p>Sand progressively: 80 → 120 → 220 → 400 grit.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
        <div class="step-title">Step 7 — Oil the Board</div>
        <p>Apply food-safe mineral oil until the board stops absorbing.</p>
    </div>

    <h2>Finished Dimensions</h2>
    <p>A typical board from a single 8 ft 1x8 produces a cutting board around:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>12"–16" long</li>
        <li>10"–12" wide</li>
        <li>1"–1.25" thick</li>
    </ul>

</div>

<div class="footer">
    <p>© 2025 Cutting Board Plans</p>
</div>

